<div id="content">
     <h1 id="toptext">Techfest - over the years</h1> 
	<p>Techfest – IIT Bombay’s annual technological festival is stepping into its ninth year of existence. In a very short time since its inception in 1998, Techfest has become the most prominent event in the calendar of all science and technology enthusiasts in India. Techfest went international in 2004 and is presently the unrivalled largest fest of its kind in Asia. </p>
	<p>Techfest enjoys a large <strong>participation of students from about 750 colleges across India</strong> and has in the past hosted teams from countries like <strong>USA, Singapore, Iran, Pakistan, Sri Lanka and Nepal</strong>. The participants at Techfest are not just restricted to students. Techfest brings together eminent thinkers, scientists and professors from different fields as well as corporate heads through a variety of exhibitions, lectures and workshops. It is this wide variety of personalities that makes Techfest such a ‘complete’ festival – covering the entire spectrum from the development of technology to its practical applications and uses.</p>
	<p>Techfest is very proud to have been associated with industry leaders in the past like<strong> Reliance, Veritas, Daimler Chrysler, Intel, Microsoft, HCC, Mastek, Honeywell, HCC, Indian Oil, The Indian Express, The Week, Chip, Digit, Zee Business</strong>  and many more big names as sponsors and media partners.</p>
	<h1>Events</h1>
	 <p>The events at Techfest, over the past eight editions, can in general be classified under Technoholix, Lecture Series, Competitions, Hub & Exhibitions, and Workshops: </p>
	 <h3>Technoholix</h3>
	 <p><img src="./img/mclaren.gif" hspace=10  vspace=5 align="right">Technoholix is the most glamorous and glitzy event of Techfest. Held in the Open Air Theatre (OAT) of IIT Bombay, that can house a capacity of 7500 people, technoholix provides a variety of entertainment through the three nights of Techfest, letting everyone soak in the electric atmosphere and just relax after a hard day’s work in our numerous competitions and workshops. The spectators are enthralled by a number of events which include cutting edge technology along with some fantastic displays.</p>
	 <p>Last year, we had exhibited a McLaren Mercedes F1 racer, the MP4 -15, accompanied by a dazzling laser show - the first time that a Formula One Car was on public display in India! </p><br>
	 <p></p>
	 <p><img src="./img/humanoid.gif" hspace=10  vspace=5 align="left">Also, humanoid robot soccer matches were played to a gallery of packed spectators who were left awed seeing the robots perform a number of tasks such as playing soccer to even dancing to popular tunes. </p> 
<p>The final night at Technoholix saw the grand finale of the Sci Tech hosted by Barry O’Brien, who has been our quizmaster for the past two years. The finals were conducted with great finesse from the setting of the questions to the high level of technology used in giving the finalists computerized answering pads and LCD monitors</p><br><br>
<h3>Lecture Series</h3>
<p>Prominent members from varied fields have come to Techfest to share their ideas and works. The speakers are all great achievers in their respective fields and however different the lectures may be, one thing for sure is that every speaker has left behind a spell bound audience – one that is more informed than ever before about numerous aspects of the field.</p>
